# NyxFoundation Vulnerability Reports

Past security vulnerability reports and fixes from audited protocols and clients,
normalized for use with the SPECA audit pipeline.

## Domains

| Domain | Description |
|---|---|
| `ethereum` | Past fixes from 11 Ethereum consensus + execution clients |
| `defi` | DeFi audit contest findings (Code4rena, Sherlock, CodeHawks) |

## Usage

```python
from datasets import load_dataset

# Ethereum client fixes
ds = load_dataset("{{ repo_id }}", "ethereum", split="train")

# DeFi audit findings
ds = load_dataset("{{ repo_id }}", "defi", split="train")
```

## Schema

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | str | Unique row identifier |
| `source_platform` | str | Client/platform slug (e.g. `geth`, `code4rena`) |
| `contest` | str | Repo slug or contest identifier |
| `issue_id` | str | Platform-local issue/PR id |
| `severity` | str | High / Medium / Low / Info |
| `title` | str | Verbatim issue title |
| `description` | str | Verbatim description |
| `source_url` | str | Link to original report |
| `introduced_in_commit` | str | Vulnerable-state commit SHA (parent of fix) |
| `domain` | str | `ethereum` or `defi` |
| `scraped_at` | str | ISO 8601 UTC timestamp |

